what is this test and when do you take it i heard from a friend that during her pregnancy she had to take a test to see if she had become diabetic since she got pregnant what kind of a test do they make you do and when do they usually have you do it i m currently weeks and my next appointment is at weeks what is that test like do they take your blood or something i am going in for my week appt next week and i will be taking the hr glucose test your dr will give you a bottle usually orange flavored drink that you can or cannot refridgerate to drink hr before the scheduled appt time to get your blood drawn i recommend getting to the office minutes after you drink it because it is very time sensitive and you don't want to have to do it again because you were late you will have to fast not eat for at least hrs before you drink it so try to get an appt first thing in the morning for the blood draw what they are testing for is your body's ability to metabalize sugar properly it is common to become diabetic during pregnancy and it usually clears up afterwards it's called gestational diabetes don't stress over any of the tests just remember that they are all precautionary measures congrats and good luck Diabetes mellitus Obstetrics Insulin Insulin resistance Pregnancy Diabetes insipidus Glucose tolerance test Diabetic retinopathy Urinary incontinence Hypertension Breastfeeding Childbirth Hyperglycemia Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Polycystic ovary syndrome Soft drink Dieting Coeliac disease Gastroparesis Blood sugar Fecal incontinence Blood type Atkins Nutritional Approach Veganism Folic acid Glycemia Abortion Fasting Dialysis Turner syndrome Elephant Birth weight Glucose meter Nutrition Blood test Psoriasis Marathon (sport) Sugar substitute Caffeine Glucokinase Stroke Diabetic coma Fanta Prenatal diagnosis Menstrual cycle Tooth Anti-diabetic drug Guinea pig Inulin Social rule Alcoholic beverage Vitamin C Kidney Aortic dissection Infant respiratory distress syndrome A